On this page, you will need to introduce your worklog. How did you complete it? How many weeks did you take to complete the program? What did you do in those weeks?
Typically, and as a standard, a worklog is carried out over about 3 months (throughout the internship period) with weekly contents as follows:
Week 1: Get familiar with AWS platforms and learn about the FCJ 2025 program
Week 2: Networking on AWS (AWS VPC, VPC Peering &amp; Transit Gateway, VPN &amp; Direct Connect, Elastic Load Balancing)
Week 3: Compute VM Services on AWS (Amazon EC2, Amazon Lightsail, Amazon EFS/FSx, AWS Application Migration Service (MGN))
Week 4: Storage Services on AWS (S3, Snow Family, Amazon Storage Gateway, Disaster Recovery on AWS, AWS Backup)
Week 5: Security Services on AWS - &ldquo;Security is job zero&rdquo; (Shared Responsibility Model, AWS Identity and Access Management, Amazon Cognito, AWS Organizations, AWS Identity Center (SSO), AWS Key Management Service - KMS, AWS Security Hub)
Week 6: Database Services on AWS (Database Concepts, Amazon RDS, Amazon Aurora, Amazon Redshift, Amazon ElastiCache)
Week 7: Doing task G&hellip;
Week 8: Doing task H&hellip;
Week 9: Doing task I&hellip;
Week 10: Doing task L&hellip;
Week 11: Doing task M&hellip;
Week 12: Doing task N&hellip;
